article.headline: William & Mary 70, Hampton 60
article.story: HAMPTON, Va. (AP) -- Calvin Baker scored a career-high 21 points to lead William & Mary to a 70-60 win over Hampton Tuesday night. Adam Payton added a career-high 18 points, and Laimis Kisielius had 11 points for the Tribe (2-1). William & Mary held the Pirates (0-2) to 36.9 percent shooting, and 37.5 percent from the line. The Tribe shot 49 percent on the night. Bruce Brown had 13 points and 10 rebounds for Hampton, and Jeff Granger added 12. Baker, William & Mary's freshman guard, was named the Colonial Athletic Association rookie of the week on Monday. This is the 11th meeting between the two teams, with the Tribe leading the series 7-4.
